      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The money isn't just sitting in some random, unsupervised bank account, which is a very important distinction! It's held by a neutral third party, usually a title company or an escrow company. These entities are specifically licensed and regulated to handle these funds, which is why they are so much safer than just leaving it with a random acquaintance or a small, unvetted operation. They are bound by strict legal rules, which is the real safeguard against things going missing or being misused.",
