      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Think of the escrow agent less like a simple guard and more like a highly organized, very cautious, and legally bound manager of the transaction. They don't just \"sit\" on the money; they actively manage the conditions—like ensuring the home inspection clears or the loan is approved—before they release the funds. If you're worried about them messing around, you should absolutely check their licensing and reputation, which is a standard part of the closing process. You want a reputable company, not some shady little operation running out of a back room, which is how you know you're dealing with professionals who won't treat your deposit like a pile of loose change.",
